reviewText: This is a 60 minute VHS containing a 1949 live TV appearance poking fun at network execs, movie shorts, coming attractions including Curly's first film appearance and original straightman Ted Healy. They sing "for the halibut" when Frank Sinatra hosts a party in rare TV footage. Also includes a pilot for a TV series that  never materialized, Moe Howard on a talk show and a government film promoting U.S. Savings Bonds by Moe, Larry and Curly Joe.
